{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἱμάτιον</b> [ῑμᾰ-], τό, <br /> in form a <i>diminutive</i> of ἷμα (i.e. εἷμα), <b>a piece of dress</b>; in usage always of <b>an outer garment</b>, formed by an oblong piece of cloth worn above the χιτών, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ecclesiazusae” 333, “IG” 22.1524.205, +others, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 24.114, etc.; λαμπρὸν ἱ. ἔχων 5th c.BC: Epicharmus Comicus [277] \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; θοἰμάτιον by crasis for τὸ ἱμ-, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 179, +others; θοἰμάτιον καθεὶς ἄχρι τῶν σφυρῶν 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 19.314; ἱματίων ἕλξεις 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus Alcaeus1.122c \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of the Roman <b>toga</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Brutus” 17, “Cor.” 14: hence ἐν ἱματίοις\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>], of civilians,= <b>togati</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Cam.” 10 \">Refs</a>]; but ἱ. Ἑλληνικόν, opposed to the toga, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Merc.Cond.” 25. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> ἱμάτια, τά, generally, <b>clothes</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.9, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Politicus” 279e, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 27.10; by crasis, θαἰμάτια 6th c.BC: Hipponax Iambographus 83.1, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 408 (Lyric poetry), “Lys.” 1093 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; of <b>grave-clothes</b>, ἐν εἱμ. τρισὶ [θάπτειν] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 12(5).593.2 (Iulis, see/iv 5th c.BC: Bacchylides Lyricus), compare 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Solon” 21. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <i>metaphorically</i>, ἱμάτια πόλεως τείχη [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 12th c.AD: Eustathius Episcopus Thessalonicensis 1871.50. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> generally, <b>cloth</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.23, 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 14.109, 2nd-3rd c.AD: Aelianus “Varia Historia” 8.7, 4th c.AD: Iamblichus Philosophus “de vita Pythagorica” 21.100. [ἱμ-\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] in <i>Attic dialect</i> Inscrr., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 12.427, 386.18, 22.1514.16, etc.; εἱμ- [prev. work]12(5) [prev. cited] (εμ- lap.), 5(1).1390.16, +others(Andania, 1st c.BC), which is easier to explain, see at {εἷμα},{εἱματισμός}.] \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G2440","accentedUnicode":"ἱμάτιον","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G2439","matchingForm":"ἱματίζω","stepTransliteration":"himatizō","gloss":"to dress","_zh_tw_Gloss":"穿上","_es_Gloss":"vestir","_zh_Gloss":"穿上"},{"strongNumber":"G2441","matchingForm":"ἱματισμός","stepTransliteration":"himatismos","gloss":"clothing","_zh_tw_Gloss":"衣服","_es_Gloss":"ropa","_zh_Gloss":"衣服"}],"shortDef":"clothing, cloak, robe","mediumDef":"clothing, cloak, robe <br /><b>a garment; the upper garment, mantle,</b> <ref='Mat.5.40; 9:16, 20, 21'>Mt. 5:40; 9:16, 20, 21</ref>; <i>plural</i> <b>the mantle and tunic together,</b> <ref='Mat.26.65'>Mt. 26:65</ref>; <i>plural</i> <i>generically</i> <b>garments, raiment,</b> <ref='Mat.11.8; 24:18'>Mt. 11:8; 24:18</ref>","stepGloss":"clothing","stepTransliteration":"himation","count":63,"_es_Definition":"traje, vestidura, ropa ; túnica, capa, manto (ropa exterior)","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) (任何形式的) 服飾<br>2) 外袍","_zh_Definition":"1) (任何形式的) 服饰<br>2) 外袍","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"áo choàng; quần áo dài","_zh_tw_Gloss":"衣服","_es_Gloss":"ropa","_zh_Gloss":"衣服"}]}